question_title: Will any AI model achieve a score of 94% or higher on the GPQA Diamond Benchmark Leaderboard before February 1, 2026?
summary: This question is very unlikely to resolve YES. The key barriers are: (1) No model has self-reported a GPQA Diamond score of 94% or higher - the ceiling is 93.8% from Gemini 3 Deep Think; (2) Epoch's leaderboard hasn't been updated past 92.6% despite newer models being available for months; (3) Only ~4 days remain, insufficient for a new model release + independent Epoch evaluation + leaderboard update. The community prediction has dropped to ~1-5%, reflecting strong consensus. The only slim possibility is Epoch evaluating Gemini 3 Deep Think and getting a score slightly higher than the self-reported 93.8%, but this would require both the evaluation happening and the result crossing 94.0% - both unlikely given the short timeframe and narrow margin.

factors.description: No self-reported GPQA Diamond score reaches 94% - highest is 93.8% (Gemini 3 Deep Think), making it nearly impossible for Epoch's independent evaluation to exceed 94%
Epoch's GPQA Diamond leaderboard still shows 92.6% as top score as of Jan 7, 2026 - no updates with newer models in 2+ months
Only ~4 days remain until Feb 1 deadline - insufficient time for new model release, Epoch evaluation, and leaderboard update
Community prediction has dropped from ~40% to ~1-5%, reflecting strong consensus this won't happen
Epoch's independent evaluations are close to self-reported scores (within CI) but not systematically higher - small chance 93.8% self-report could evaluate to 94%+
A surprise new model could theoretically be released and evaluated, but extremely unlikely in 4 days
